    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix pnf_nr_read_dispatch_message socket handling in NFAPI\n\n### Summary\nThe `pnf_nr_read_dispatch_message` function in the NFAPI PNF module had inconsistent error handling that could cause the NR PNF to incorrectly report socket connectivity status. When `sctp_recvmsg` failed during message reading or when memory allocation failed, the function would return inconsistent values (-1 vs 0) which the calling `pnf_nr_message_pump` interpreted incorrectly, leading to stalled PNF-VNF communication.\n\nThe issue manifested as the PNF getting stuck in a loop where it believed the socket was still connected even when the underlying SCTP connection had failed. This caused the 5G gNB to hang during PNF initialization.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/pnf/src/pnf.c`: Fixed return value consistency in malloc failure case (line 2192)\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/pnf/src/pnf.c`: Added proper socket disconnection detection when `sctp_recvmsg` fails (line 2206)\n\n"
}